VDeepa Krishnan, from Chennai, presented a scintillating veena concert at the Rasika Ranjana Sabha, Tiruchi, recently. The programme was sponsored by the Tamil Nadu Iyal Isai Nataka Mandram.Deepa Krishnan began her concert with a bright varnam in Nattai composed by Balamuralikrishna. She demonstrated her mastery over the instrument in her rendition of &#8216;Vathapi Ganapatim' (Hamsadhwani) and &#8216;Maravari Ramani' (Nasikabhushani).Soothing delineationHer rendition of Swati Tirunal's kirtana in Mayamalawagowla depicted her creativity. She then moved on to play the fast and exuberant &#8216;Raguvamsasudha.' &#8216;Kadambari Priya' in Mohanam was the main song for the day. The raga alapana and tanam were soothing to the ears. Niraval was wholesome and her fine flow of swaras depicted her originality.Her choice of popular tukkadas such as &#8216;Chinnanjiru Kiliye,' &#8216;Kavadi Chindu' and &#8216;Karpagame' were enjoyable.The feather-like touches on the veena by Deepa produced an enchanting melody. She has honed her skills in playing the instrument under the tutelage of Kamala Aswathama. Deepa was accompanied by G. Aravind on the mridangam.
